      "text": "You don't have to white-knuckle through big feelings. Genuine emotion-regulation tools, none of which involve nicotine:\n\n• Name it to tame it. Putting a feeling into words measurably reduces its intensity: labelling an emotion calms the brain's alarm centre.\n\n• Express and connect. Talk to someone, write it out, let it move. Emotions are meant to be shared and discharged, not bottled and smoked over.\n\n• Move the body. Anger and anxiety especially live in the body; a walk or physical activity metabolises them.\n\n• Self-soothe for real. Comfort that actually comforts: a person, rest, warmth, music, air — instead of a momentary chemical blip that fixes nothing.\n\n• For celebration: be fully present in it. The joy is the reward; you don't need to step away from your own good moment to service an addiction."
